Linux kernel
============

The Linux kernel provides the operating system for the runtime
VM. synthmodem redistributes a compiled kernel image and a
selection of loadable modules at:

  vm/kernel/bzImage
  vm/kernel/modules/

These are taken from the Debian bookworm binary package
`linux-image-6.1.0-42-686-pae-unsigned` (Debian source package
`linux` version 6.1.159-1, i386). The kernel and its modules
are used only when the slmodemd-pjsip backend is active (or
during the slmodemd-pjsip phase of the auto backend) and run
inside QEMU; the native backend runs entirely on the host
Node.js runtime and does not load them.

Upstream project:  https://kernel.org/
Upstream source:   https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git
Debian package:    https://packages.debian.org/bookworm/linux-image-686-pae

License
-------

The Linux kernel is licensed under the GNU General Public
License, version 2 only (GPL-2.0-only), with an explicit
exception for the user-space syscall interface known as
"Linux-syscall-note". The kernel's own COPYING file states the
SPDX identifier as:

  GPL-2.0 WITH Linux-syscall-note

The "or later" option of the GPL does NOT apply to the kernel.
The complete GPL-2.0 text is at `licenses/GPL-2.0.txt`. The
Linux-syscall-note exception text is preserved in the upstream
source tree at `LICENSES/exceptions/Linux-syscall-note` inside
`vm/sources/linux_6.1.159.orig.tar.xz`.

Individual kernel source files carry their own SPDX identifiers
and copyright headers; those headers are preserved verbatim in
the vendored source tarball.

Corresponding source
--------------------

GPL-2.0 §3(a) requires that the kernel binaries redistributed in
`vm/kernel/` travel with their complete corresponding source.
That obligation is satisfied by committing the upstream Debian
source set to this repository at:

  vm/sources/linux_6.1.159.orig.tar.xz   (split: .partaa + .partab)
  vm/sources/linux_6.1.159-1.debian.tar.xz
  vm/sources/linux_6.1.159-1.dsc

The upstream tarball is split into two parts because GitHub's
100 MB per-file limit is below the kernel tarball's 131 MB size;
see `vm/sources/README.md` for the maintainer-side handling
strategy and the reassembly procedure. SHA256 sums for all parts
are pinned in `vm/sources/SHA256SUMS`. The top-level `COPYING`
enumerates these paths in its GPL corresponding-source statement.

Modifications from upstream
---------------------------

None. synthmodem redistributes the unmodified Debian binary
package contents (kernel image plus the subset of modules
required by the runtime VM, primarily virtio drivers). If
synthmodem ever ships a patched kernel, this notice must be
updated to record the nature of the modifications, per GPL-2.0
§2(a).
